      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(imessage): keep split-send coalescing opt-in",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nRelated to #91243. This PR keeps the compatibility path and narrows its behavior; #91243 should remain open for the eventual teardown decision unless maintainers explicitly decide this is the final resolution.\n\nThis keeps the opt-in `channels.imessage.coalesceSameSenderDms` compatibility path instead of deleting it. The branch now addresses the review risk by preserving the fallback for command-only URL split-sends while tightening the metadata-aware behavior when `imsg` exposes `balloon_bundle_id`.\n\n## What changed\n\n- Preserved `channels.imessage.coalesceSameSenderDms` in the config/type surface.\n- Keeps iMessage DM split-send debouncing only when the opt-in flag is enabled and no explicit global or iMessage inbound debounce is configured.\n- Widens that opt-in default from 2500 ms to 7000 ms after live Messages.app proof showed URL preview rows can arrive ~5-6 seconds after the text row.\n- Uses `balloon_bundle_id: \"com.apple.messages.URLBalloonProvider\"` to merge only adjacent standalone URL-preview rows with the preceding command row when metadata is available.\n- Dispatches already-complete URL-balloon messages separately so an unrelated pending DM is not absorbed into a complete `check https://...` message.\n- Accepts both `https://...` and scheme-less `www...` standalone preview rows.\n- Keeps ordinary buffered DMs separate once any balloon metadata has been observed, including metadata observed on stale/suppressed rows.\n- Keeps the metadata-less fallback for older or pre-latch `imsg` sessions, where a command + URL split-send cannot be distinguished from ordinary same-sender rows.\n- Updates iMessage and BlueBubbles migration docs to describe the preserved opt-in behavior and fallback limits.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior or issue addressed: iMessage command + URL preview split-sends should still reach the agent as one turn without regressing ordinary DM separation when structural `imsg` balloon metadata is available.\n\nReal environment tested: Local macOS Messages.app + `imsg 0.11.1` connected to Messages.app with `privateApi.available: true` and `v2Ready: true`; foreground OpenClaw gateway from this PR checkout during the live proof; plus the iMessage monitor through mocked `imsg` RPC notifications and the real monitor/debounce/coalesce code path on final head `5811377e220`.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch:\n\n```bash\npnpm openclaw --version\nimsg status --json\npnpm openclaw gateway stop\npnpm openclaw gateway run --port 18789 --verbose\npnpm openclaw channels status --probe --channel imessage --json\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/imessage/src/monitor/coalesce.test.ts extensions/imessage/src/monitor.last-route.test.ts extensions/imessage/src/monitor/parse-notification.test.ts\nnode --import tsx scripts/generate-config-doc-baseline.ts --check\nnode --import tsx scripts/generate-bundled-channel-config-metadata.ts --check\nnode scripts/format-docs.mjs --check\npnpm build\n.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode branch --base origin/main\n```\n\nEvidence after fix:\n\n- Live probe before the fix exposed the original gap: a single user-sent iMessage bubble with `/help ocproof-1782075768` and `https://example.com/ocproof-1782075768` wrote the text row at local 14:05:59 and the URL preview row at 14:06:04, so the old 2500 ms window dispatched them separately as message IDs 782 and 784.\n- Live probe after widening used one user-sent iMessage bubble with `/help ocproof-1782081763` and `https://example.com/ocproof-1782081763`. Messages.app wrote row 6223 at local 15:44:32 with text `/help ocproof-1782081763`, then row 6224 at local 15:44:38 with text `https://example.com/ocproof-1782081763` and `balloon_bundle_id='com.apple.messages.URLBalloonProvider'`.\n- The PR-head foreground gateway emitted one merged inbound turn at local 15:44:46: preview contained both `/help ocproof-1782081763` and the URL, and the dispatch path used a single `messageId=787` through `message received`, `message queued`, `message processed`, and `outcome=completed`.\n- Follow-up safety commits after the live run only narrowed URL-balloon merging to standalone preview rows and added scheme-less `www.` preview support. The live `https://example.com/...` row is still covered by the same standalone-preview path on final head.\n- Separate ordinary DMs from the same sender stayed separate in the live run: `ordinary one ocproof-1782075425` and `ordinary two ocproof-1782075425` dispatched as separate message IDs 776 and 778.\n- `3 passed (3)` test files, `54 passed (54)` tests in the iMessage monitor/parser shard.\n- Config doc baseline check: `OK docs/.generated/config-baseline.sha256`.\n- Bundled channel config metadata check exited cleanly.\n- Docs formatting check: `Docs formatting clean (665 files)`.\n- `pnpm build` completed successfully before the final safety commits; the final safety commits touch only the iMessage coalescer/tests and docs hash/formatting.\n- Autoreview exited clean on final head: `no accepted/actionable findings reported`, `overall: patch is correct`.\n\nObserved result after fix: A real Messages.app command+URL split-send with a 6 second text-to-URL-preview gap merged into one iMessage inbound turn; URL split-send buckets also merge in tests when a standalone URL balloon row is present; complete URL-balloon messages dispatch separately from unrelated buffered DMs; unrelated buffered rows dispatch separately once metadata support is known; stale balloon rows are suppressed from delivery but still latch metadata support for later live rows; old metadata-less sessions preserve the existing fallback merge behavior.\n\nWhat was not tested: Full GitHub CI is rerunning on final head after the rebase and force-push.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/imessage/src/monitor/coalesce.test.ts extensions/imessage/src/monitor.last-route.test.ts extensions/imessage/src/monitor/parse-notification.test.ts`\n- `node --import tsx scripts/generate-config-doc-baseline.ts --check`\n- `node --import tsx scripts/generate-bundled-channel-config-metadata.ts --check`\n- `node scripts/format-docs.mjs --check`\n- `pnpm build`\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode branch --base origin/main`\n",
        "branch": "imessage/retire-split-send-coalescing-91243",
